Package domparser.Rules.RuleObjects

Interface Summary
RuleObjectInterface Interface for RuleObjects
 

Class Summary
AbstractRuleObject Defines the RuleObject and provides basic methods for RuleObject processing.
childComponentCount Checks the number of component-type children from the 1st level children from a given tree.
ChildCount Checks the number of element-type children from the 1st level children from a given tree.
childCountCheck Checks the number of 1st level children from a given tree.
childFieldCount Checks the number of field-type children from the 1st level children from a given tree.
childSegmentCount Checks the number of segment-type children from the 1st level children from a given tree.
childSegmentGroupCount Checks the number of segmentgroup-type children from the 1st level children from a given tree.
childSubComponentCount Checks the number of subcomponent-type children from the 1st level children from a given tree.
compareAttribute Compares text equality of an attribute of the supplied nodes.
compareConformanceTypeAttribute Compares equality of attribute of the supplied node.
compareConstantValueAttribute Compares text equality of an attribute of the supplied nodes.
compareDatatypeAttribute Compares text equality of the datatype attribute of the supplied nodes.
compareItemNoAttribute Compares text equality of an attribute of the supplied nodes.
compareLengthAttribute Compares text equality of an attribute of the supplied nodes.
compareMinMaxAttribute Ensures that the min-max range of Profile A is being constrained by the min-max range of Profile B.
compareNameAttribute Compares equality of attribute of the supplied node.
compareTableAttribute Compares text equality of an attribute of the supplied nodes.
existenceMaxAttribute Determines if the Max attribute exists in both DocumentObjects given.
existenceMinAttribute Determines if the Min attribute exists in both DocumentObjects given.
optionalityHierarchyCheck If the node(s) has/have an optionality, they must follow a constrain hierarchy.
optionalityMinMaxProperty Ensures that for a given optionality, the Min/Max values coincide.
optionalityPredicateRequired If the node(s) has/have an optionality of C or CE, it must also have a Predicate child node.
